goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving a good idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield vs nitrogen level
goals.rationale: A scatter plot will show the relationship between yield and nitrogen level, allowing us to see if there is a positive or negative correlation between the two variables.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of yield by site
goals.rationale: A stacked bar chart will show the total yield at each site, broken down by variety, making it easy to see which sites have higher or lower yields overall.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield for each variety?
goals.rationale: A histogram will show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing us to see if the yield is normally distributed or skewed, and if there are any outliers.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="yield", data=data, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['variety']).mean().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['yield', 'nitro']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='nitro', y='yield', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Nitrogen Level')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['site', 'variety'])['yield'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="site", y="yield", hue="variety", data=data)
    ax.set_title('How does the yield vary across different sites?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Site')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.legend(title='Variety', loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['yield', 'variety']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='variety', kde=True, multiple='stack', palette='bright')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield for each variety?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Variety')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
